flowchart TB
    N1["1. Entry domain: L2 batch | guest ELF | prover configuration"]
    N2["2. Normalization: shape batch, witness, and public input into proof-system constraints"]
    N3["3. Core mechanism: Prepare SP1 stdin | Run prover | Verify proof envelope"]
    N4["4. State and commitment: state root, public values, verification key, and proof digest"]
    N5["5. Evidence or result: proof bytes | verification report | state commitment"]
    N6["6. Consumer boundary: bridge relayer | L1 verifier adapter | devnet scripts"]
    N7["7. Failure path: proving fails, local verification fails, public output mismatches, or verifier rejects"]
    N8["8. Extension point: proof backend, verifier adapter, report format, and DA binding"]
    N1 --> N2
    N1 --> N3
    N1 --> N4
    N1 --> N5
    N1 --> N6
    N1 --> N7
    N1 --> N8
    N2 -. constrains .-> N4
    N4 -. produces .-> N5
    N5 -. consumed by .-> N6
